<div id="review_1616372889" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1616372889" />
    <a title="D.C. Triana" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/54037421-d-c-triana"><img alt="D.C. Triana" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1616372889?book_show_action=true">Apr 20, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="D.C. Triana" class="user" itemprop="url" name="D.C. Triana" href="/user/show/54037421-d-c-triana">D.C. Triana</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/27845545-beast-blood">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1616372889" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer922923194867258099">“Look toward the sky and behold the red moon…take notice an army of beasts guarding the newborn who will be one with the guardian in Heaven &amp; Earth.”<br/>I absolutely loved this book! It drew me in from the first page. It begins in 1515, Scotland, as you follow a woman, Alexandria, as she escapes the wrath of her husband through a dark tunnel. Then you’re thrown to present day Michigan where you meet Esmeralda and Gabrio…a nice, loving couple. You soon find out that they are alpha werewolves, or…Beas</span>
  <span id="freeText922923194867258099" style="display:none">“Look toward the sky and behold the red moon…take notice an army of beasts guarding the newborn who will be one with the guardian in Heaven &amp; Earth.”<br />I absolutely loved this book! It drew me in from the first page. It begins in 1515, Scotland, as you follow a woman, Alexandria, as she escapes the wrath of her husband through a dark tunnel. Then you’re thrown to present day Michigan where you meet Esmeralda and Gabrio…a nice, loving couple. You soon find out that they are alpha werewolves, or…Beast Bloods. I couldn’t put the book down as I was thrown into a story filled with werewolves, covens, blood tasters, and an ancient prophecy about a blood moon, and a newborn hybrid that’s about to change everyone’s life forever. And then there’s Laycerath…his name alone, drips evil. <br />This book is such a great read, the author does a wonderful job in depicting the characters, so much so, that you immediately find your connection to them. Esmeralda and Gabrio’s bond is so great that you are continuously rooting for these two characters to overcome their circumstances. The blood tasters depict darkness, and are so complex that you can’t help, but appreciate their characters. I definitely recommend this book whether you are a paranormal fan or not. A wonderful read!<br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/27845545.Beast_Blood_Volume_Two_Truer_Sin" title="Beast Blood Volume Two Truer Sin by M.A. Levi" rel="nofollow noopener">Beast Blood: Volume Two: Truer Sin</a><br />I was gifted a copy of this book in exchange for an honest review.</span>
  <a data-text-id="922923194867258099" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


