        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1616547540?book_show_action=true">Apr 21, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="J.S. Strange" class="user" itemprop="url" name="J.S. Strange" href="/user/show/51926477-j-s-strange">J.S. Strange</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/27845545-beast-blood">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1616547540" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7576089532956777554">This book might not have been my most preferred genre, but it was a very entertaining read. The beginning had me hooked, and the author is so good at describing the setting and her characters feelings, I couldn&apos;t help but feel what they felt. Without giving too much away, right at the beginning, there is someone searching for his wife - he&apos;s angry, and he seems important. His wife is meanwhile escaping through a claustrophobic tunnel. This made me quite spooked, and I wanted to find out if she e</span>
  <span id="freeText7576089532956777554" style="display:none">This book might not have been my most preferred genre, but it was a very entertaining read. The beginning had me hooked, and the author is so good at describing the setting and her characters feelings, I couldn't help but feel what they felt. Without giving too much away, right at the beginning, there is someone searching for his wife - he's angry, and he seems important. His wife is meanwhile escaping through a claustrophobic tunnel. This made me quite spooked, and I wanted to find out if she escaped! Then we meet two other characters, who start moving the story along, and we soon learn that this is a story of 'beast bloods', or werewolves. <br /><br />Whilst novels of werewolves might be overdone - it is a shame that people can't seem to write vampire/werewolf stories without being compared to Twilight - this book didn't feel over done. There was a flair of originality to it, and the characters were so well developed you actually felt for them, which is sometimes missed in stories like this. <br /><br />I'm a fan of this author, and I'm looking forward to M.A. Levi's works in the future. I'll be following! </span>
  <a data-text-id="7576089532956777554" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


