<span id="freeTextContainer4377096789177399"><i>4.5 stars</i><br/><br/>This is the second book in the Beast Series, and the story and characters get increasingly darker and complex. Drawing on biblical themes, the book recasts the age-old battle of good vs evil, with the werewolves acting as a resolute barrier between the demonic forces and humanity at large. The transformation scenes are beautifully written; you can almost hear every crunch of bone and every tear of muscle. The revelation of Sheryl&apos;s character is the highlight of the book. A strong sequel</span>
  <span id="freeText4377096789177399" style="display:none"><i>4.5 stars</i><br /><br />This is the second book in the Beast Series, and the story and characters get increasingly darker and complex. Drawing on biblical themes, the book recasts the age-old battle of good vs evil, with the werewolves acting as a resolute barrier between the demonic forces and humanity at large. The transformation scenes are beautifully written; you can almost hear every crunch of bone and every tear of muscle. The revelation of Sheryl's character is the highlight of the book. A strong sequel to the first book, with an end that brims with potential for an even stronger third.</span>
