        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1818944962" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7981945448352536169">Truer Sin was another gripping tale of Beast Bloods, Blood Tasters, demons and angels. A twist that propels Adam and Eve to a place I never imagined. <br/>From the beginning, I was pulled into Gab and Esse&apos;s life. There were parts that made me smile, laugh and I couldn&apos;t help but be drawn in when they fell into each others arms. I was curious of the role Sheryl played since she was from the first book and seemed as if she was a loving mother figure to Gab. With that being said, I was with what happen</span>
  <span id="freeText7981945448352536169" style="display:none">Truer Sin was another gripping tale of Beast Bloods, Blood Tasters, demons and angels. A twist that propels Adam and Eve to a place I never imagined. <br />From the beginning, I was pulled into Gab and Esse's life. There were parts that made me smile, laugh and I couldn't help but be drawn in when they fell into each others arms. I was curious of the role Sheryl played since she was from the first book and seemed as if she was a loving mother figure to Gab. With that being said, I was with what happened, sending me on a roller coaster ride with each chapter I read.<br />M.A. Levi gave enough info to keep you interested, wanting more. A spec of detail that made your mind build what was happening and when the story actually revealed itself, I was bombarded with an avalanche of reality. At the end, my mouth hung open.<br />I can honestly say book 2, Truer Sin, was my favorite of Beast Blood's so far. There was a perfect ending, satisfying me. When I read the epilogue, hello book 3.</span>
