<div id="review_1616815898" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1616815898" />
    <a title="Pike" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1311663-pike"><img alt="Pike" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1459112830p2/1311663.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1616815898?book_show_action=true">Apr 21, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pike" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pike" href="/user/show/1311663-pike">Pike</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1616815898" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11686743255913402829">Werewolves, vampires, angels and demons fill the pages of Beast Blood, all of which I&apos;m a fan of but sadly I had trouble reading this book. The central story took a while to get into motion. Without spoiling the plot, the meat of Esmeralda&apos;s dilemma didn&apos;t really come into play until two-thirds of the way into the story. And as a werewolf fan I hoped for more tooth and claw action but that waited to nearly the end. I will say that I haven&apos;t read the first part of the series. Not sure if there we</span>
  <span id="freeText11686743255913402829" style="display:none">Werewolves, vampires, angels and demons fill the pages of Beast Blood, all of which I'm a fan of but sadly I had trouble reading this book. The central story took a while to get into motion. Without spoiling the plot, the meat of Esmeralda's dilemma didn't really come into play until two-thirds of the way into the story. And as a werewolf fan I hoped for more tooth and claw action but that waited to nearly the end. I will say that I haven't read the first part of the series. Not sure if there were other details I should have known about prior to reading Beast Blood but I wasn't confused or lost because of it. <br /><br />For those who enjoy epic tales and love-conquers-all stories give this one a try. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11686743255913402829" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


