<div id="review_1900406795" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1900406795" />
    <a title="Sheree" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/59040428-sheree"><img alt="Sheree" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1487425651p2/59040428.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1900406795?book_show_action=true">Feb 02, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sheree" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sheree" href="/user/show/59040428-sheree">Sheree</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1900406795" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13902006752536755973">I have read other books by this author as I particular like her style of writing. She brings out the dark intrigue of urban fantasy books. The book starts in Scotland (I live in the Scottish Borders) which is what draw me in to the story straight away. Gabrio and Essie have a nice relationship, both of them bouncing off one another nicely. They are a good match for one another. My only criticism is the book was slightly too long. Otherwise a good read, well worth a look.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


